<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>face someone down • face up to someone</xh5><p> <i>face someone down—</i>confront smb. in an attempt to subdue or dominate the person: The project is too important to be placed in jeopardy by the vanity of one man, and those who are too cowardly to <u>face him down</u>.</p><p><i>face up to someone—</i>challenge a person boldly; refuse to be intimidated: Confrontation may not be your desired choice but unless you <u>face up to</u> a person or situation your views will never be heard.</p> </entry>
